description: Return the timing potentiometer to its previous setting (0.50) to verify if the lamp resumes cycling as before. This will help determine if the potentiometer setting is responsible for the lamp remaining off., outcome='The timing potentiometer was successfully returned to its previous setting (0.50). Upon inspection, the main lamp remains off and shows no observable internal faults.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('adjust_potentiometer', 20.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> output terminals of the control module (to load module),
description: Measure the voltage across the output terminals of the control module (going into the load module) to determine if 12V is being delivered, especially after returning the potentiometer to its original setting and the lamp still does not turn on., outcome='The voltage measured at the Control Output Cable (+) is 0.3592 V, and at the Control Output Cable (−) is 0.0003 V. There is no significant voltage (~12V expected) being delivered to the load module.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> input terminals of the control module (from power supply module),
description: Measure the voltage across the input terminals of the control module to verify if 12V is present at the input to the control module from the power supply module. This will help determine if power is reaching the control module and if the issue lies upstream or within the control module relay/signal circuit., outcome="Voltage measurement at 'Control Input Cable (+)' shows approximately 11.99 V, and at 'Control Input Cable (−)' it is near 0 V. This indicates that nominal voltage is present across the control module input terminals. No polarity inversion is detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Switched cables indicator LED (control module),
description: Observe the indicator LED inside the control module that is in parallel with the relay output. Check whether it is turning on and off as the system operates, which will indicate if the relay is switching and attempting to supply voltage to the load., outcome='The requested action could not be mapped to any recognized diagnostic operation. Only actions from the available action list are supported (e.g. measure_voltage, test_continuity, inspect_connections, verify_repair, …).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=0.0, cost_breakdown=[], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Relay (control module),
description: Test the continuity of the relay contacts in the control module to verify if the relay is functioning properly and making the connection between the input and output cables when it is supposed to be closed., outcome='The inspection panel was successfully opened, allowing access to internal components. The measured resistance across the control relay contacts is 0.01 Ω, which matches the nominal value. Continuity of the control relay is confirmed as nominal.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=25.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Switched cables indicator LED (control module),
description: Measure the voltage across the switched cables indicator LED in the control module to check if voltage is present there when the relay is closed, confirming if both sides of the relay/control circuit are behaving as expected., outcome='Voltage at the PSU Status LED (green) anode is 1.29 V and cathode is 0.0 V, indicating a typical forward-biased LED. At the Control Relay, the p terminal is at 11.99 V and the n terminal is at 0.36 V. No polarity inversion was detected in these measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Load module input terminals,
description: Measure the voltage at the input terminals of the load module to verify if any voltage is reaching the load module from the control module, despite the relay output being at 11.99 V (p) and 0.36 V (n). This will help confirm if there is a wiring issue, connection fault, or voltage drop before the load module's diode and lamps., outcome='Voltage measured at Load Input Cable (+) is 0.3592 V and at Load Input Cable (−) is 0.0003 V. This indicates very low voltage present at the load module input. No POLARITY INVERSION detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Interconnection cables (between control and load modules),
description: Test the continuity of both cables connecting the control module output to the load module input to check for any open or high-resistance connections that could explain the near-zero voltage at the load module input despite correct voltage at the control module output., outcome="All tested cables ('Control Output Cable (+)', 'Control Output Cable (−)', 'Load Input Cable (+)', 'Load Input Cable (−)') show nominal continuity with resistance values at 0.1 Ω, matching expected nominal values. No open or high-resistance connections were detected in the cables between the control module output and load module input.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Load module diode,
description: Test the voltage across the diode in the load module to determine if the diode itself is dropping most or all of the voltage. This will establish whether the diode is possibly open, failed, or otherwise blocking current to the bulbs., outcome='Voltage measurement across the load protection diode shows 0.3592 V at the anode and 0.0003 V at the cathode, indicating a forward voltage drop across the diode. This suggests the diode is conducting and not open or blocking current to the bulbs.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=25.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
